#X text 33 61 The [del.in~] and [del.out~] objects from ELSE are like [delwrite~] and [dlread4~] \, respectively. It uses a different interpolation method (spline) and offers more functionalitites not present in the native delay objects (at least not yet) \, like being able to resize the delay line in [del.in~] \, "freeze" the recording and change the delay name on the dealay reading object. We can also set the delay time in samples instead of ms. Like the Vanilla originals \, they also take multichannels \, butthey are set automatically in [del.in~] according to the input., f 72;
